s.</span><hr size=1> I've always wanted to start a web comic. Unfortunately, while my drawing skills aren't crap, they are not good enough for a webcomic. If anyone wants to help (Write, draw, colour, whatever) I would appreciate it. At the very least read this, it's the beginning to a web comic, an overview really. If you like it I can post a little more of the story, if not you could ask to see another concept. Here it is:<br>
<br>
Title: Voyd<br>
<br>
Eighteen-year-old Alex Yazama has lived a very odd life. Son of the prominent Dr. Yumari Yazama there, he was constantly in the middle of a custody battle between his father and his “uncle” Curtis. This uncle had the most bizarre habit of taking Alex to shooting ranges, dojos, and other various training facilities. His uncle said he was ex-military and he enjoyed this kind of stuff, so Alex never questioned. Along with this custody battle Alex had gaps in his memory from times when he would just blackout randomly. Also, for as long as he could remember, there had been a tattoo of the number “666” across his forehead. Although this was very strange, after living eighteen years with it, it seemed to have lost its importance. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  Life was going at a normal pace, well as normal as it had ever been for Alex. When one evening, when he and his father were sitting down at dinner, there was a break in. It was chaos, men breaking in through the windows, crashing through the doors, and all carrying highly advanced firearms. That was the last time Alex saw his father alive, it was also the first time he saw his father dead. The air became thick with bullets, which ripped through his father. Eyes filled with tears and mind filled with revenge Alex grabbed a decorative sword from it’s mantle and turned to face the intruders. He blacked out. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp When he woke he was in a dark alley and soaked in blood. Confused and frightened he tried to retrace his steps. From deeper in the alley Alex hears a scream and runs off to investigate. He finds a woman being cornered by two knife-wielding thugs. Doing what felt right, Alex leapt in to defend the woman. Dispatching the thugs with relative ease, Alex turns to make sure the woman is all right. When he looks at her, he notices that she is staring at his stomach in horror. Looking down, Alex realizes that some of the blood on him was his own, from a bullet wound on his stomach. He passes out. <br>
<br>
Whaddya think?<br>
